  "title": "Standard Operating Procedures for Groundnut Breeding and Testing",
  "abstract": "The Standard Operating Procedures (SOP) is a reference or manual on breeding methodologies and testing procedures used at the International Crops Research Institute for the Semi-Arid Tropics (ICRISAT) to breed new groundnut varieties. It describes the tools that are currently being used for phenotyping and genotyping specific traits in groundnut. The SOP will be useful to groundnut researchers, scientific and technical staff and scholars and the NARS (National Agriculture Research System) partners...",
